 SOS 69069 ZK LENDING - PRIVACY-PRESERVING CREDIT PROOF SYSTEM



1. CORE PRINCIPLE

The SOS ZK Lending system is designed with a strict separation rule:
SOS data must never directly or indirectly influence lending decisions or token issuance.
SOS is only a user-controlled data environment used to generate cryptographic proofs.



2. SYSTEM OVERVIEW

The architecture is composed of three independent layers:
(1) SOS SYSTEM
Generates interaction events (Mint, Trust, Join)
Stores no financial logic
Provides only raw user activity data
Has no role in lending decisions
(2) USER PROVER (LOCAL LAYER)
Runs on user device or secure environment
Reads SOS data locally
Generates Zero-Knowledge proofs
Extracts only compliance signals
Does NOT expose raw SOS data
(3) LENDING SYSTEM
Receives only ZK proofs
Verifies cryptographic validity
Makes independent loan decisions
Has no access to SOS data or graph structure



3. KEY DESIGN RULE

The lending system must satisfy:
Loan decisions are fully independent of SOS data.
Formally:
SOS ⟂ Lending Decision



4. ZK PROOF FUNCTIONALITY

Instead of sharing SOS data, the user proves:
“I meet lending conditions without revealing underlying data.”
Example proof conditions (abstracted):
Minimum activity threshold satisfied
Stable behavioral consistency over time
No fraudulent or abnormal interaction patterns
Compliance with predefined risk constraints
Critical property:
No SOS events are revealed
No identity graph is exposed
No interaction history is shared
Only proof validity is shown.



5. LENDING CONTRACT MODEL

A minimal lending contract only verifies proofs:
Accepts ZK proof input
Validates proof cryptographically
Approves or rejects loan request
Does not access SOS or any external data source



6. DATA FLOW

User interaction flow:
User interacts with SOS system
SOS data remains local or user-controlled
User generates ZK proof on their device
User submits proof to lending system
Lending system verifies proof only
Loan decision is made independently



7. SECURITY MODEL

What lenders can see:
ZK proof validity result (true / false)
No underlying data
What lenders cannot see:
SOS event history
Interaction graph
Identity linkage structure
Behavioral patterns



8. SYSTEM GUARANTEE

The system enforces:
No SOS dependency in lending logic
No data leakage from SOS to lender
No inference of SOS state in contract execution



9. FORMAL PROPERTY

The system satisfies:
Loan Decision ⟂ SOS Data
Meaning:
Loan outcomes are mathematically and operationally independent of SOS.



10. ROLE OF SOS IN THIS SYSTEM

SOS is strictly:
a behavioral event log
a user-controlled data source
a non-financial system component
It is NOT:
a credit scoring system
a financial oracle
a lending input layer



11. FINAL SUMMARY

The SOS ZK Lending system enables:
Privacy-preserving credit assessment
Zero exposure of behavioral data
Independent lending decisions based only on cryptographic proofs
Strict separation between social data and financial systems
🔥 CORE PRINCIPLE
SOS provides data.
ZK transforms it into proof.
Lending systems only verify proof — never the data.
